This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Young girls and boys (0â€“5 years), particularly the most deprived and hard-to-reach, are immunized, well nourished, healthy, protected, registered at birth and prepared for school, including in humanitarian situations.

description.narrative: In Mali, access to quality maternal, newborn, and infant care improved significantly during 2021 despite the COVID-19 Pandemic. In 2021, 100 per cent of health districts implemented at least three interventions to improve the quality of maternal and newborn care and nutrition services and no stockouts of routine vaccines were registered in the country. In total, 86 per cent of target health centres were equipped with WASH facilities and 85 per cent of UNICEF supported health facilities achieved a Severe Acute Malnutrition (SAM) cure rate of more than 75 per cent. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:05/01/2022
